 "The suspect will be charged with rape and will appear before the Willowvale Magistrate’s Court on Monday on a charge of attempted rape." A 22-year-old man is expected in court after he was arrested by Willowvale police for the attempted rape of a 59-year-old woman. "The suspect was arrested at Maya Location, Nqadu Village, Willowvale on Thursday," described police spokesperson, Captain jackson Manatha. "It is alleged that the suspect is the neighbour of the victim. "He normally requests permission  to sleep at the house of the victim and is allowed to sleep in the house of the victim, but on a different bed." Captain Manatha said that on Sunday, the suspect as usual went to sleep in the house of the victim at Maya Location, Nqadu Village, Willowvale.  "The victim woke up at about 23h10 on Sunday 03 March 2019 and found the suspect trying to rape her," he said. "She saw the suspect as the lights were not switched off. The victim fought back and the suspect ran for his dear life." He said that the suspect was traced and finally arrested on Thursday. "The suspect will be charged with rape and will appear before the Willowvale Magistrate’s Court on Monday on a charge of attempted rape." Butterworth police have appealed to women to be cautious and not afford male strangers places to sleep over as they will become victims of sexual crimes. Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here.  